1 certify with the director of taxation the number of hours of instruction and
2 the amount of the tax credit claimed in each tax year. The preceptor shall
3 also certify that such preceptor did not receive payment during such tax
4 year from any source for the training of any student or students.
5 (d) The educational institution or sponsored program of a student
6 receiving preceptorship shall provide a student receiving the preceptorship
7 an annual statement that verifies the amount of hours such preceptor has
8 provided to such institution's or program's students in each tax year. The
9 community-based faculty preceptor shall provide the director of taxation a
10 copy of the annual statement.
11 (e) The credit allowed by this section shall not exceed the amount of
12 tax imposed under the Kansas income tax act. Such credit shall be
13 deducted from the taxpayer's income for the taxable year in which the
14 preceptorship occurred and shall not be refundable.
15 (f) (1) The amount of such credit awarded to a taxpayer in a
16 taxable year pursuant to this section shall not exceed $750.
17 (2) The total amount of credits allowed under this section for each
18 taxable year shall not exceed $50,000.
19 (g) As used in this section:
20 (1) "Community-based faculty preceptor" or "preceptor" means an
21 individual who is a nursing home administrator, registered nurse or
22 registered dietitian and licensed as such by this state.
23 (2) "Postsecondary institution" means any not-for-profit institution of
24 postsecondary education with its main campus or principal place of
25 operation in Kansas that offers a promise eligible program, is operated
26 independently and not controlled or administered by any state agency or
27 subdivision of the state, maintains open enrollment and is accredited by a
28 nationally recognized accrediting agency for higher education in the
29 United States.
30 (3) "Preceptorship" means an uncompensated mentoring experience
31 in which a community-based faculty preceptor provides a program of
32 personalized instruction, training and supervision to a Kansas board of
33 regents student or a student of a postsecondary institution.
34 (4) "Student" means an individual participating in a postsecondary
35 institution or as a sponsor a sponsored program as defined in K.S.A. 65-
36 3501, and amendments thereto, that provides a training program for the
37 training of nursing home administrator, registered nurse or certified dietary
38 manager.
39 (5) "Sponsored program" means the same as "sponsor" as
40 defined in K.S.A. 65-3501, and amendments thereto.
41 Sec. 2. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
42 publication in the statute book.

